<paragraph id="4454707BFFEBFFB1FF27FB5532D1FACD" blockId="17.[138,1185,402,1424]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2387">
Remarks: This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="83EB0BF8FFEBFFB1FD0EFB5A325DFAAD" box="[652,812,1271,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Periacma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="2387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erawanensis">
<emphasis id="769FAC69FFEBFFB1FD0EFB5A325DFAAD" box="[652,812,1271,1295]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2387">P. erawanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the somewhat finger-like gnathos, the valva not expanded distally, and the aedeagus divided into two distal processes. In the latter species, the gnathos is triangularly shaped, the valva is medially expanded and the aedeagus bears three distal processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4454707BFFEBFFB1FF27FADA326AFA32" blockId="17.[138,1185,402,1424]" box="[165,795,1400,1424]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2387">
